  "prompt": "Will ISPs block whatsapp, kik, and wechat if we lose net neutrality?",
  "response": "The concern about Internet Service Providers (ISPs) blocking or throttling specific services like WhatsApp, Kik, or WeChat in the absence of net neutrality is a valid one. Net neutrality is the principle that ISPs should treat all data on the internet the same, without discriminating or charging differently by user, content, website, platform, application, or method of communication.\n\nIf net neutrality regulations are repealed, ISPs could potentially prioritize their own services or partner services over others, which might result in slower speeds or accessibility issues for competing messaging apps and platforms. Although outright blocking these apps may not be a widespread practice, ISPs could implement practices that negatively impact their usability, such as reducing bandwidth or making them less accessible compared to their preferred services.\n\nUltimately, while it\u2019s not certain that ISPs would take such drastic measures, the possibility of prioritization or throttling raises significant concerns about access and competition in the digital landscape.",
